      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (fluid properties, rotational speed, inlet flow rates, geometry dimensions) sourced from traceable measurements with stated uncertainty; input uncertainty propagation confirms NIH prediction uncertainty remains within ±25% at 95% confidence.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity and density taken from literature with ±2% uncertainty bounds. Pump geometry digitized from manufacturer drawings with dimensional tolerances documented. Rotational speed and flow rate boundary conditions matched experimental rig settings within ±1%. Uncertainty propagation via Monte Carlo (1000 samples) yielded NIH uncertainty of ±18% at 95% CI."
    },
